chasing the deer ( later re-titled culloden 1746 ) is a 1994 british war film directed by graham holloway and starring brian blessed , lewis rae , iain cuthbertson , fish and mathew zajac .   it depicts the 1745 jacobite rebellion , in which bonnie prince charlie landed in scotland , trying to claim the british throne .   the title metaphorically alludes to the jacobites as the quarry in a deer hunt .   the phrase " a-chasing the deer " appears in the refrain of the romantic scottish poem by robert burns , my heart 's in the highlands ( 1789 ) .